<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="editor-welcome-entry" >Among the bright stars of software development and its star systems of agile and lean development, there are those whose jobs are to stitch together a constellation of people processes and things that keep our stars and systems in alignment - letting us aim high in our ambitions.<br> <br> 
In this issue, we get a glimpse at some of those who help connect the dots for our teams and customers.
 New CIO Drew Kramer outlines his roadmap for world-class IT, Bhavin Modri provides an update on TechOps’ approach to keep product development humming, and Rodney Wong shows how the rigor behind QA for mobile apps help forge great products.<br> <br> All of this helps us light the skies 
and lead the way – in deed and thought – to modern software development.
 In that spirit, we get a halftime update on the <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.pivotal.io/platform-as-a-service/cloud-platform-roadshow" target="_blank">Cloud Platform Roadshow</a>, Pivotal leaves its data imprint at <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: 
none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/inside-pivotal/events/2014-strata-confrence-hadoop-world" target="_blank">Strata + Hadoop</a> this week in NY, and former AWS leader and now Pivotal evangelist, Simon Elisha, kicks off our new Pivotal podcast series, <a style="color: #3ea7bc; 
text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.pivotal.io/podcasts" target="_blank"><em>All Things Pivotal</em></a>.<br> <br> Enjoy!</div>
