<a href="#product-update" name="product-update"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="product-update-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block; padding-left: 20px; padding-top: 10px;" src="http://play.gopivotal.com/rs/pivotal/images/nl-portrait-bmodi.png" alt="Bhavin Modi" align="right"> <span style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">PRODUCT UPDATE</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;">Data Fabric TechOps: The Machinery of Product Development</span><br> <span style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;"><a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://gopivotal-com.socialcast.com/users/930140-bhavinmodi">Bhavin Modi</a>, TechOps Manager</span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="product-update-entry" >
<p>Data Fabric TechOps manages the machinery behind data product development.
 We recently joined Drew Kramer&rsquo;s IT team under Sean Murray, and we&rsquo;re very excited to be part of a group that has been a natural partner for TechOps.
 With millions of dollars invested in infrastructure, we strive for self-service and automation to make the cycle from product development to delivery as efficient as possible.
 While our primary &ldquo;customers&rdquo; are Data Fabric engineers, we replicate useful resources and services across the company &ndash; partnering with GSS, App Fabric, and other teams in the process.<br /> <br /> We cover the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Tools and Applications (JIRA, Confluence, GIT/Stash, Jenkins, SCOTzilla, others)</li>
<li>Cloud Infrastructure (private cloud and self-service development environment for data teams)</li>
<li>Physical Infrastructure (compute clusters to test scalability and performance)</li>
</ul>
<p>A key part of managing a global infrastructure is building tools and platforms that can be leveraged throughout Pivotal.
 SCOTzilla is one such recent application, used by engineering and legal teams across the Data Fabric, App Fabric and Cloud Foundry to ensure that products are bundled with proper licenses.<br /> <br /> We also partner with EMC IT to ensure efficient workflows across companies.
 We&rsquo;re currently working with them to prepare and migrate our&nbsp;greenplum tools&nbsp;to <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://pivotal.io/" target="_blank">pivotal.io</a>&nbsp;in 2015.
 This will provide more Pivotal employees across the globe with access to key collaboration tools.&nbsp;We&rsquo;re also&nbsp;building a centralized repository service that will allow data product teams to publish software for internal consumption, prior to release for customers.<br /> <br /> 
Finally, I would like to welcome our new TechOps leader Sean Murray! Data Fabric Tech Ops is well placed in 2015 to ensure a reliable, efficient and high-performing infrastructure.</p>
</div>
