<a href="#agile-update" name="agile-update"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="agile-update-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block; padding-left: 20px; padding-top: 10px;" src="http://play.gopivotal.com/rs/pivotal/images/nl-portrait-rwong.png" alt="Rodney Wong" align="right"> <span style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">AGILE UPDATE</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;">Mobile Quality – The Sum of All Testing </span><br> <span style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;"><a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://gopivotal-com.socialcast.com/users/1032794-rodneywong">Rodney Wong</a>, Agile Test Engineering Manager, Pivotal Labs</span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="agile-update-entry" ><p>Many of you are probably unaware that Pivotal Labs has a Quality Assurance (QA) practice. Although <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test-driven_development" target="_blank">Test-Driven Development </a>(TDD) is a key component of agile development, mobile apps also require specialized QA not covered by TDD.<br /> <br /> In setting a strict bar on quality, we help the business by providing the best possible products to customers. We always test on real devices &ndash; with over 1,300 phones and tablets in our inventory! This helps to verify carrier or location-based testing (e.g., NFL on Verizon, NBA on Sprint, Virgin on Boost) and ensure performance across a range of devices.<br /> <br /> We work on weekly iterations, delivering builds through <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.xlstudio.com" target="_blank">Pivotal App Studio</a>. Our process follows these stages:</p>
<ul>
<li>Weekly Story and Exploratory Testing: Explore product functionality, discover potential flaws and provide UI/UX feedback to improve the product design and user flow.</li>
<li>Release Candidate (RC) Testing: We focus on a broad range of supported devices, to execute a tailor-made RC test plan, regress the entire application, perform edge case testing and provide a detailed summary of the results.</li>
<li>Automated Testing: This supplements our weekly story verification, as a UI-based testing strategy where we write scripts to automate testing on Android, iOS, and Web applications. <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://pivotallabs.com/resource/automation-testing-mobile/" target="_blank">You can read more about Automation Testing on mobile in this paper we wrote</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Working with our teams for our biggest customers, Pivotal Labs&rsquo; QA teams are the gatekeepers of product quality.<br /> <br /> <img style="display: block;" src="http://play.gopivotal.com/rs/pivotal/images/toronto-QAdem-.png" alt="QA Automation Demo table at the recent Toronto office opening celebration." /><br /> <em>QA Automation Demo table at the recent Toronto office opening celebration.</em></p></div>
