<a href="#people-update" name="people-update"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="people-update-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block; padding-left: 20px; padding-top: 10px;" src="http://play.gopivotal.com/rs/pivotal/images/nl-portrait-dkramer.png" alt="Drew Kramer" align="right"> <span style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">PEOPLE UPDATE</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;">Pivotal IT - Make <strong>IT</strong> happen</span><br> <span style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;"><a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://gopivotal-com.socialcast.com/users/1072686-drewkramer">Drew Kramer</a>, Chief Information Officer</span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="people-update-entry" ><p>I&rsquo;m delighted to join the Pivotal mission. After over two decades in technology, with the last 11 at VMware (helping set a course and building out its IT operation), I believe <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/pivotal-it/?pli=1" target="_blank">Pivotal IT</a> moves with the best of them. My aim is to use our best technology assets to make things simpler and easier for you &ndash; easier to sell, win and share things across our company and with customers.<br /> <br /> While Pivotal is lean, and we know how to leverage cloud-based services, we have unique complexities &ndash; including a number of network policies to manage and businesses to serve. But we also have untapped strengths and tremendous opportunities in IT. My priorities to leverage these in 2015 can be summed up as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Deliver an Excellent Employee Experience</strong><br /> IT will have an active role in our efforts around making this a special place to work by improving many employee experiences &ndash; including more reliable feedback mechanisms.</li>
<li><strong>Create a World-Class IT Team Delivering ITaaS</strong><br /> We have the tools to become a model for next generation IT. <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://blogs.gartner.com/lydia_leong/2014/08/25/bimodal-it-vmworld-and-the-future-of-vmware/" target="_blank">&ldquo;Bi-modal IT&rdquo;</a> is an approach that enables IT to be agile and fast where the business requires it, and &lsquo;traditional&rsquo; and doing-it-right if that better serves the business. With that principle in mind, we&rsquo;re considering a &ldquo;many modes&rdquo; approach. IT will interlock with our top business goals and avoid common IT pitfalls of silos and &ldquo;<a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_invented_here" target="_blank">not-invented-here</a>&rdquo; thinking.</li>
<li><strong>Dogfood for Success</strong><br /> We build outstanding platforms and apps, and we help customers master data. We&rsquo;ll funnel that experience to our teams, building apps that help a highly-mobile Field, provide competitive business intelligence for executives and engage our people. Look for a team to coalesce around this priority!</li>
<li><strong>Consolidate and Coordinate IT Activities</strong><br /> 2015 will be the year that we align IT teams across the company around these common goals. This will help eliminate process gaps and overlaps. </li>
</ul>
<p>And last, but certainly not least, you have the support of a responsive, world-class IT team behind these efforts &ndash; which I&rsquo;m privileged to lead. Making IT easy is hard work, but I have confidence in our strengths and teams. We&rsquo;re just getting started, so I look forward to updating you again in 2015!</p></div>
